    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "we've adjusted the pool size and checked the load balancer configs, but it's still happening randomly. it feels like something is just sabotaging the process right when it's supposed to work. like, everything is configured perfectly on paper, but then these errors just pop up out of nowhere for no logical reason. it's incredibly frustrating. any other ideas?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When everything *looks* perfect, but the failures are sporadic, it often points to non-deterministic behavior, like a very specific type of resource contention or an external dependency hiccup. Consider the possibility of connection saturation at the *gateway's* end, even if their CPU looks fine—they might be hitting a hard limit on concurrent connections allowed by their own infrastructure. Also, review your retry logic; if the retries are too aggressive or if the downstream service is in a brief \"thundering herd\" state, your retries might just be adding to the problem, causing cascading failures.",
      "source": "target",
